es the litigation labor & employment division encompassing a broad range of litigation as well as employment law benefits and labor law she received her ba in 1988 with high honors phi beta kappa from the university of california at berkeley and her jd in 1993 from stanford law school where she served as notes editor of the stanford law review international regional representatives australia new zealand stuart loh llm 09 stu fissure org brazil jose mauro decoussau machado 09 55 11.3247 8730 josemauro pinheironeto com br carlos motta 04 55 11.8536 1974 carlos motta17 gmail com belgium frederic debussere 04 32 2.533 53.51 frederic debussere stibbe com central america edwin a mendieta 04 505 274.4225 emendieta bac com ni france bernard j phillips 74 33 1.44 17.99 53 guillaume p werner 04 33 1 40 74 68 00 gwerner cgsh com india girija krishan varma 03 91 9313338142 girijav stanfordalumni org italy gabriele antonazzo 04 212 225.2000 gantonazzo cgsh com london united kingdom pamela hope black 97 44 20.7071 4233 pblack gibsondunn com mexico rodrigo orenday serratos 04 52 55.2272 8457 rodrigoorendays stanfordalumni org south america maximiliano g knull 09 54 11 5256 1265 maximiliano knull lh lf com south korea kyung yoon lee 03 822 3703.1181 kylee stanfordalumni org spain dr alejandro paya 99 34 93.290 5447 alejandro paya cuatrecasas com switzerland tobias f somary 04 41 44.285 1111 tobias somary cms veh com contact information stanford law school office of external relations crown quadrangle 559 nathan abbott way stanford ca 94305 8610 alumni relations law stanford edu 650 723.2730 cloudy 50 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour the school offices & adminis office of external re alumni regional law c main navigation the school campus people offices & administration facts history giving the program degrees courses clinics programs & centers tuition & financial aid the experience student life scholarly life areas of interest beyond campus careers e